step_by_step_solution.details:
Start with the standard structure from Topic 1:

```java
public class PayrollCalculator {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Variables go here
    }
}
```

Add inside main:

```java
String employeeName = "Priya Sharma";
int employeeAge = 28;
double monthlySalary = 85000.00;
double taxRate = 15.5;
boolean isFullTime = true;
```

Notice the naming: descriptive, camelCase, no abbreviations.

Calculate tax and take-home pay:

```java
double taxAmount = monthlySalary * (taxRate / 100);
double takeHomePay = monthlySalary - taxAmount;
```

Why `taxRate / 100`? Because taxRate is stored as 15.5 (percentage), not 0.155 (decimal). Dividing by 100 converts.

Print a clean payroll summary:

```java
System.out.println("========================================");
System.out.println("          PAYROLL SUMMARY");
System.out.println("========================================");
System.out.println("Employee:        " + employeeName);
System.out.println("Age:             " + employeeAge);
System.out.println("Full-time:       " + isFullTime);
System.out.println("----------------------------------------");
System.out.println("Monthly Salary:  ₹" + monthlySalary);
System.out.println("Tax Rate:        " + taxRate + "%");
System.out.println("Tax Amount:      ₹" + taxAmount);
System.out.println("Take-Home Pay:   ₹" + takeHomePay);
System.out.println("========================================");
```

Note: We use `+` to concatenate strings with variables. Java auto-converts variables to their string representation.

worked_example.final_code:
public class PayrollCalculator {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Employee data
        String employeeName = "Priya Sharma";
        int employeeAge = 28;
        double monthlySalary = 85000.00;
        double taxRate = 15.5;
        boolean isFullTime = true;

        // Calculations
        double taxAmount = monthlySalary * (taxRate / 100);
        double takeHomePay = monthlySalary - taxAmount;

        // Output
        System.out.println("========================================");
        System.out.println("          PAYROLL SUMMARY");
        System.out.println("========================================");
        System.out.println("Employee:        " + employeeName);
        System.out.println("Age:             " + employeeAge);
        System.out.println("Full-time:       " + isFullTime);
        System.out.println("----------------------------------------");
        System.out.println("Monthly Salary:  ₹" + monthlySalary);
        System.out.println("Tax Rate:        " + taxRate + "%");
        System.out.println("Tax Amount:      ₹" + taxAmount);
        System.out.println("Take-Home Pay:   ₹" + takeHomePay);
        System.out.println("========================================");
    }
}
